      "99": { "$value": "#fffbff" },
      "100": { "$value": "#ffffff" }
    }
  },
  "semantic": {
    "$type": "color",
    "$description": "System tier — theme-dependent roles. These are the tokens components consume, exported 1:1 as StyleX vars of the same name. positive*/negative* follow the same custom-color formula as error (the same 40/100/90/10 light and 80/20/30/90 dark pattern) so they read as first-class roles, not a bolted-on exception.",
